The paper discusses the development of algorithms for learning belief network structures under causal insufficiency, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of efficient reasoning methods for belief network structures, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of joint probability distributions and hidden variables, which are topics in data science (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a remedy for the failure of the FCI algorithm, which involves the manipulation of network links, a topic in systems and control (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
